\pard\f0\fs28  The wide variation found within this species includes two different levels of polyploidy, but it is not yet known whether these are correlated with any morphological or geographical features. There seem to be no grounds so far for recognizing any of the variants at subspecific level. The species is connected by numerous, probably hybridogeneous, intermediates with {\b 35}, {\b 41}, {\b 43}, {\b 56} and {\b 61}.
