\pard\f0\fs28 {\b  T. dolomiticus} Coste,{\i  Bull. Soc. Bot. Fr.}{\b  40}: 130 (1893), from S. France, should probably be included in {\b 55} as a subspecies. It is characterized by a diploid chromosome number (2n = 28), flowering stems hairy all round, leaves 5-7 × 1-1·5 mm, hairy, and calyx 3-4 mm, with tube shorter than lips.
\par

\pard\f0\fs28  A tetraploid plant (2n = 54), which is more widespread in S. France, characterized by stems incompletely hairy on opposite sides, leaves c. 11 × 2·5 mm, glabrous, subcoriaceous, with slightly more prominent venation than in {\b 55}, and calyx 3·5-4·5 mm with almost cylindrical tube as long or slightly longer than lips, does not seem to differ significantly from{\b  T. embergeri} Roussine,{\i  Rec. Trav. Montpellier }({\i Sér. Bot.}) {\b 5}: 79 (1952), also from France, for which, however, the chromosome number 2n = 48 has been reported.
